b'Rathika Ramasamy
Rathika ramaswamy is a well known wildlife Photographer from New Delhi.Her specialization is bird photography.She experienced nature photography for the past eight years. Her work has been showcased in national and international publications.
                      RAREST BIRD SHE PHOTOGRAPHED
Srilankan frogmouth bird, which is a nocturnal bird and camouflages itself very well as it looks just like a dry tree branch.It is endemic to Western ghats and Srilanka.
                         RATHIKA'S FAVOURITE LOCATION
Keoladeo National Park, Bharatpur,Rajasthan is her favourite location. Okhla bird sanctuary which is close to her home is also her favourite location.
                  HER VIEW IN WILDLIFE CONSERVATION
RATHIKA says "Photographs of wildlife connect nature to people, and thereby help increase awareness about wildlife and its conservation. It is particularly important to spread this awareness among youth and children. Photographs depicting damages to the environment make common people sit up and take notice. It can help people understand how certain human activities can wreak havoc on natural habitats and on wildlife. I have contributed my photographs to nonprofit organizations that use them for campaigns to increase awareness."
                 Rathika's favourite subjects in photography
Rathika says she loves to take candid people photography and she loves to travel to different places.
                               RATHIKA'S INSPIRATIONS
Moose Peterson,  Arthur Morris,John Shaw were three great inspiring photographers for Rathika's photography.
                 
                     INFORMATION COURTESY:121 CLICKS'
